JOHANNESBURG - The South African National Defence Force (SANDF) has dismissed claims that former Eskom CEO Brian Molefe is now working for the army.
	
	The defence force says Molefe is a Reserve Force member, and an honorary colonel. It says Molefe was appointed to the reserve force while he was CEO of the Public Investment Corporation. READ: Former Eskom CEO gets R30-mil handshake Molefe is ranked a Colonel, and is in control of the audit section of what the army calls its Pool of Specialists. Weekend reports claim Molefe has been earning nearly R60,000 a month since he started in August.                                                                                                                                                                   The force says, like other Reserve members, Molefe has been called into service on several occasions, and is paid accordingly. eNCA